00:35:49,347 --> 00:35:54,081
Dr. Murphy, I'd
like you to tell us

501
00:35:54,152 --> 00:35:55,814
why you want to
become a surgeon.

502
00:36:14,239 --> 00:36:16,333
Why do I want them
to be my friends?

503
00:36:16,408 --> 00:36:17,928
Everybody needs friends, Shaun.

504
00:36:18,543 --> 00:36:21,604
It's gonna be cool, okay?
Play hide-and-seek, maybe?

505
00:36:21,946 --> 00:36:23,847
- Okay.
- Tag in the warehouse.

506
00:37:04,556 --> 00:37:06,218
I told you, it's fun, right?

507
00:37:13,798 --> 00:37:15,266
Hey. You know what?

508
00:37:52,437 --> 00:37:54,997
The day that the rain
smelled like ice cream,

509
00:37:57,075 --> 00:38:01,638
my bunny went to
heaven in front of my eyes.

510
00:38:05,583 --> 00:38:08,417
The day that the copper
pipes in the old building

511
00:38:08,486 --> 00:38:09,749
smelled like burnt food,

512
00:38:12,323 --> 00:38:13,882
my brother

513
00:38:16,361 --> 00:38:18,990
went to heaven
in front of my eyes.

514
00:38:22,901 --> 00:38:26,736
I couldn't save them. It's sad.

515
00:38:29,908 --> 00:38:32,605
Neither one had the
chance to become an adult.

516
00:38:34,846 --> 00:38:37,873
They should have become adults.

517
00:38:40,752 --> 00:38:44,154
They should have had
children of their own

518
00:38:44,222 --> 00:38:47,124
and loved those children.

519
00:38:52,096 --> 00:38:55,931
And I want to make that
possible for other people.

520
00:39:07,145 --> 00:39:10,707
And I want to make a lot of money
so that I can have a television.

